<taxonomicName id="4C274185D864FFF0BD9EE7212B56FC91" authorityName="Gordon and Hanley" authorityYear="2017" box="[712,832,835,859]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Ponaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="112" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="daviesi">
<emphasis id="B953E614D864FFF0BD9EE7212ACCFC91" box="[712,730,836,859]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="111">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B953E614D864FFF0BDBCE7262B56FC91" box="[746,832,835,859]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="111">daviesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but distinguished from that species by yellowish brown legs, male genitalia with sides rounded throughout, female spermathecal capsule abruptly bent in basal 1/3; and Brazilian 
<typeStatus id="549C84A4D864FFF0BD51E7E12A2AFC56" box="[519,572,900,924]" pageId="112" pageNumber="111">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
